Interface Distribution

All Superinterfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<Parfactor>
All Known Implementing Classes:
StdDistribution
public interface Distribution
extends java.lang.Iterable<Parfactor>

A set of parfactors that represents a joint probability distribution.

Classes that implement this interface should not allow null elements.

Author:
Felipe Takiyama

Method Detail

add

Distribution add(Parfactor p)
Returns a distribution with the specified parfactor added. The order of the elements in the distribution may not be preserved. In other words, adding a parfactor to this distribution does not mean that it will be the last to be retrieved by iterator().

Parameters:
p - The parfactor to add to this distribution
Returns:
A copy of this distribution with the specified parfactor added.

addAll

Distribution addAll(Distribution d)
Returns a distribution that is the result of the union of the specified distribution and this distribution. Duplications are removed from the resulting distribution.

Parameters:
d - The distribution to unify with this distribution
Returns:
The union of this ditribution with the specified distribution.

toSet

java.util.Set<Parfactor> toSet()
Returns a set containing all elements of this distribution.

The returned set will be "safe" in that no references to it are maintained by this distribution. (In other words, this method must allocate a new set even if this distribution is backed by an array). The caller is thus free to modify the returned array.

Returns:
A set containing all elements of this distribution.
